development<\/a> during four decades. A strong objector to <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nazism\" title=\"Nazism\">National Socialism<\/a>, he was instrumental in re-establishing and organizing German science after <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/World_War_II\" title=\"World War II\">World War II<\/a>.<\/p>","name":"Max von Laue","place_of_birth":"Pfaffendorf ,  Germany","place_of_death":"Berlin   Germany","text":"Max von Laue , Physics, 1914","year":1914.0}